programme.title: The Texas Chainsaw Massacre Part 2
programme.desc: A retired Texas Ranger (Dennis Hopper) pursues a killer named Leatherface (Bill Johnson) and his family of chainsaw-wielding cannibals.

programme.title: The Condemned
programme.desc: A death-row inmate from a Central American jail is among the prisoners taken to a remote island for a to-the-death match broadcast live over the Internet.

programme.title: The Condemned 2
programme.desc: A former bounty hunter (Randy Orton) lands in a tournament where convicts fight to the death for an online audience.

programme.title: Act of Valor
programme.desc: During a mission to rescue a kidnapped CIA agent, Navy SEALs uncover a worldwide terrorist plot against the U.S.

programme.title: Southpaw
programme.desc: After losing everything to a senseless tragedy, a boxer (Jake Gyllenhaal) turns to a retired fighter (Forest Whitaker) for guidance as he struggles toward redemption.

programme.title: Warrior
programme.desc: An Iraq War veteran (Tom Hardy) finds himself on a collision course with his estranged brother (Joel Edgerton) when both set their sights on winning a tournament in mixed martial arts.
A desperate man takes part in an underworld game of Russian roulette in which gamblers place bets on who will survive.

programme.title: A Force of One
programme.desc: A veteran (Chuck Norris) teaches martial arts to a California detective (Jennifer O'Neill) and her colleagues, and joins them on a case.

programme.title: El Rey's Top 5
programme.desc: Host Vanessa Gritton and her guests Danielle Radford and Zena Dixon list their top five zombie apocalypse gear.

programme.title: El Rey's Top 5
programme.desc: Vanessa is joined by Danielle Perez and Ed Greer.

programme.title: Frankenstein
programme.desc: In present-day New Orleans, a detective's (Parker Posey) homicide investigation leads to the discovery of an evil, ageless doctor (Thomas Kretschmann) and his creation (Vincent Perez).

programme.title: I, Frankenstein
programme.desc: Still alive in modern times, Frankenstein's creature (Aaron Eckhart) becomes caught in the middle, as gargoyles and demons wage war for the souls of mankind.

programme.title: Road to Paloma
programme.desc: After avenging the rape and murder of his mother, a man (Jason Momoa) dodges the FBI while traveling across the West to spread her ashes.

programme.title: Bubba Ho-Tep
programme.desc: A mummy stalks nursing-home residents claiming to be Elvis Presley (Bruce Campbell) and President John F. Kennedy (Ossie Davis).

programme.title: Legionnaire
programme.desc: A 1920s playboy (Jean-Claude Van Damme) returns from a stint in the French Foreign Legion to reclaim his lover, a mobster's mistress.
